  <b>
   NOTE
  </b>
  : This is not the location country code that is returned, but the language code of the OS.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">os_get_language()
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 String
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">switch (os_get_language())
{
    case "es": ini_open("spanish.ini"); break;
    case "fr": ini_open("french.ini"); break;
    case "it": ini_open("italian.ini"); break;
    default: ini_open("english.ini"); break;
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the OS language and opens a different
  <span>
   *.ini
  </span>
  file depending on the returned value.
